You can use the [hasNext()](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/7.1/classes/FindCursor.html#hasNext)
method to check if a cursor can retrieve more data, and then use
the [next()](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/7.1/classes/FindCursor.html#next)
method to retrieve the subsequent element of the cursor:

```javascript
  const cursor = myColl.find({});

  while (await cursor.hasNext()) {
    console.log(await cursor.next());
  }
```

